  "text": "Finally, models of MSA that recapitulate α-synuclein aggregation and toxicity provide a platform for testing therapies that aim to interrupt or reverse this key pathogenic event. In the α-synuclein/p25α expressing OLN-93 model, Kragh and colleagues [CITATION_1] tested three different inhibitors of α-synuclein aggregation (Congo Red, ASI1D peptide, and baicalein). All these agents significantly attenuated the microtubule retraction and apoptotic protein activation seen in untreated cells.",
